<br>
Strafing in a circle is predictable.  Learn how to hit people who strafe-move and you'll do fine.  <br>
<br>
And yes, pure melee's can eat pet casters.  Assuming the right conditions and skill of those involved. <p>Kilithyr Tekn'dius
<BR> 
Officer of The Revelation</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uunluckyguy13.showPublicProfile?language=EN>unluckyguy13</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/01 9:15:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP Question: How do I beat....</span><hr size=1> speaking as a person that plays TFC almost as religiously as EQ...a good FPS player will be able to hit a moving target regardless (unless you're movement is impeded), also, don't you have a bow and arrows?  You could just back off and pluck at him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ucoldsunsz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ColdsunSZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/01 9:25:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP Question: How do I beat....</span><hr size=1> I would get some MR and run, or die fighting if you can't, it's pretty much impossible to beat a necro around the same level as a monk unless you're in a dungeonish area where it's close packed.<br>
<br>
In your case if you really want to try, but he keeps circling around you you need to figure out a way to circle better so you can keep up with him.  Never never attack the pet, cause that won't help when he dots you like mad.<br>
<br>
You just have to hope you have no lag, a nice steady connect and keep on the necro so he can't cast until he dies.  This is really really hard if you're in an open area so you should just run.  Plus, if the necro has shadow step memorized you pretty much can't win unless he just plain sucks.<br>
<br>
There are some pretty bad players out there too, so if you know you're going to die you should try fighting, maybe that necro is not a good player and you might beat him :)<br>
<br>
You can also try training the pet to hostile stuff and then feigning there to train the necro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ucangan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cangan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/01 11:37:55 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://freepages.ugo.com/trashy/files/crackfst.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP Question: How do I beat....</span><hr size=1> Let's just say you have stable resistances for one.  If he cant engulf you he cant kill you.  When pet is argoed FD and it will send it back to master.  Or you can do a few things with this argo the pet on some high level mobs after they eat up the pet they will go directly for the necro killing him easily.  <br>
<br>
That works well but if you want to do it on your own fd pet off then stay on the necro like flies on shit.  If you allow him to tap constantly he can regain more health then you can take form him giving him the edge for victory.  But the fact is necros are always a tough fight no matter what level. <p><b>
