Caffron <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/usortex2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sortex2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>drunken' poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/01 12:20:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP Question: How do I beat....</span><hr size=1> Well ive played a pvp necro a good amount.<br>
<br>
Best ways to get rid of the pet are snare, darkness, root, fear/ get sow, or j boots. Pets have almost no mr, so unless the pet is yellow or higher to you or buffed the spells/ procs should stick.<br>
<br>
Next best way is to train the pet on a hostile npc, that happened to me so much I would cast invis everytime the pet took off, just to get rid of it.<br>
<br>
If all else fails, try to &quot;vector&quot; away, hold down foward, left and left mouse at the same time, you will move faster than the pet. Get away and camp out to clear aggro. Then find a way to get rid of (or train) the pet when you get back.<br>
<br>
